com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class NodeContentFileReaderJCIFSListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.NodeContentFileReaderJCIFSListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener

    public class NodeContentFileReaderJCIFSListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    Based on a configured attribute name(s), load content into the given node from a network location using the JCIF library specified in the given Node Attribute (default is "om_full_file_path"). Can be used as a post-export listener on the Source side or a pre-import listener on the Target side. NOTE - THIS LISTENER DOWNLOADS THE FILE AS A JAVA TEMP FILE AND MUST BE DELETED USING ANOTHER LISTENER ONCE THE NODE HAS BEEN PROCESSED!!!!

    If attribute name is a comma-separated list, then try each attribute in turn until one is found that (1) has a value, and (2) points to an existing file.

    If setFolderAndNameOnNode is TRUE, then set om_folder and om_name to the full folder path and filename/ extension, respectively. This only applies to the top-level node, not any associated nodes.

    MigrationNode Attributes Read

    • om_full_file_path

    MigrationNode Attributes Written

    • om_folder (if setFolderAndNameOnNode is set)
    • om_name (if setFolderAndNameOnNode is set)
